Nigerian pop singer Oluwatobiloba Daniel Anidugbe, popularly known as Kizz Daniel and his former record label boss, Emperor Geezy, CEO of G-Worldwide Entertainment may have buried the hatchet. In a short video and pictures which emerged on social media, the excited singer and his former boss were seen having a good time with his new song, while preparing for his UK tour which has also gathered media buzz. A reliable source revealed that “The narrative is that Kizz Daniel and Emperor Geezy have finally ended their feud in and out of court.” In a music video on Instagram, Emperor Geezy was dancing to Kizz Daniel’s latest hit single, ‘Oshe’. According to the source, the ambience resonated with love, this is as pictures of both parties now at peace flood social media. On IG, Kizz Daniel captioned the post of Emperor Geezy, “Peace, Love and Respect. At the end of it all, we just need to maintain peace and show love and respect to one another.” In a reaction to the development, a close associate who pleaded anonymity, notes that they are all happy. He said, “We have pictures of us signing paper works and all that, but I do not want us to rekindle the thing by showing paper works again because the case has lingered for a very long time.” He added: “Kizz Daniel and Emperor Geezy have established a positive vibe and moves as good friends.” POLL It would be recalled that the court case lingered for close to a decade and has made the artiste change his stage name from Kiss Daniel to Kizz Daniel. Mary J. Blige